citation.case_name: Elmer W. Kelley and the General Street Signal Corporation v. The City of Atlantic City and Harry Bacharach.

html:
302 U.S. 722

58 S.Ct. 43

82 L.Ed. 558

Elmer W. KELLEY and The General Street Signal Corporation, petitioners,
v.
The CITY OF ATLANTIC CITY and Harry Bacharach.*

No. 304.

Supreme Court of the United States

October 11, 1937

Messrs. Martin Conboy, of New York City, and Harold E. Stonebraker, of Rochester, N. Y., for petitioners.

1

For opinion below, see 89 F.(2d) 659.

2

Petition for writ of certiorari to the United States Circuit Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit denied.

*

Rehearing denied 303 U.S. 666, 58 S.Ct. 520, 82 L.Ed. ——; Second petition for rehearing denied 304 U.S. 588, 58 S.Ct. 1036, 82 L.Ed. ——.
